<?xml version="1.0"?><eml:eml xmlns:eml="eml://ecoinformatics.org/eml-2.0.1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" packageId="ljc.35.1" system="knb" xsi:schemaLocation="eml://ecoinformatics.org/eml-2.0.1 eml.xsd" scope="system"><dataset scope="document"><title>生態旅遊之遊客滿意度、解說效果與經濟效益評估(3/5)</title><creator id="1163496150265" scope="document"><individualName><surName>Jiunn-Cheng Lin</surName></individualName><organizationName>TFRI</organizationName><positionName>associate research fellow</positionName><address scope="document"><deliveryPoint>6 Chiaotou, Dawang Village</deliveryPoint><city>Taimali</city><administrativeArea>Taidung</administrativeArea><postalCode>963</postalCode><country>Taiwan</country></address><phone phonetype="voice">+886-89-781302 ext 10</phone><phone phonetype="fax">+886-89-782900</phone><electronicMailAddress>ljc@tfri.gov.tw</electronicMailAddress></creator><abstract><para>Ecotourism is often considered as a responsible travel to natural areas. The process of such travels can contribute significantly to environmental conservation and local people&apos;s benefit. Ecotourism&apos;s worth lies in its potential to provide three win situations – one win for the environment, one win for the economy and the other win for the local community and existing social and cultural structures. When engaged in ecotourism planning and development, the issues, such as, how to reduce environment impact, how to enhance visitor satisfaction by increasing visitor&apos;s nature experiences, and how to promote economic benefit by improving the inter-relationship between local community and ecotourism, are very important. Therefore, the study items including visitor satisfaction, interpretive service effects and economic benefits of ecotourism will be separately analyzed in this project in five years.</para></abstract><keywordSet><keyword>ecotourism</keyword><keyword>visitor satisfaction</keyword></keywordSet><intellectualRights><para>無限制</para></intellectualRights><coverage scope="document"><geographicCoverage scope="document"><geographicDescription>Taiwan</geographicDescription><boundingCoordinates><westBoundingCoordinate>120.625</westBoundingCoordinate><eastBoundingCoordinate>120.625</eastBoundingCoordinate><northBoundingCoordinate>24.125</northBoundingCoordinate><southBoundingCoordinate>23.25</southBoundingCoordinate></boundingCoordinates></geographicCoverage><temporalCoverage scope="document"><singleDateTime><calendarDate>2006</calendarDate></singleDateTime></temporalCoverage></coverage><contact scope="document"><references>1163496150265</references></contact><methods><methodStep><description><section><title>（一）研究期刊文獻資料分類與整理</title><para>本研究的整合資料為歷年有關台灣地區森林遊憩經濟效益研究之已發表期刊文獻整理而來，調查的項目包括消費者剩餘效益、效益評估方法、森林遊憩區品質、位置、資源種類、所有權、開發程度、森林活動種類及其活動包括森林浴、賞花、賞鳥、戲水、健行、體驗自然等等。</para></section></description></methodStep><methodStep><description><section><title>（二）遊憩經濟效益移轉模型設定</title><para>使用整合迴歸方法及非市場經濟價值評估法來估計森林遊憩經濟效益移轉函數，並分別以直線與指數迴歸模式，使用MLE估計技術進行比較，以取得最適模式。</para></section></description></methodStep><methodStep><description><section><title>（三）遊憩經濟效益估計</title><para>個別遊憩活動的平均效益可經由所取得最適模式之其他變數設定為平均下，依其β值及標準誤來表示該資源的經濟效益，同時檢測此預測模式的準確性。</para></section></description></methodStep><methodStep><description><section><title>（四）報告撰寫</title><para>依據結果進行報告撰寫。</para></section></description></methodStep></methods><access authSystem="knb" order="denyFirst" scope="document"><allow><principal>public</principal><permission>read</permission></allow></access></dataset></eml:eml>